President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key roles in the government. Erik K. Raven is nominated for Under Secretary of the Navy in the Department of Defense. Raven currently serves as the Majority Clerk of the Senate Defense Appropriations Subcommittee and has extensive experience in national security and legislative positions. Kristyn E. Jones is nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Financial Management and Comptroller. Jones is currently a Managing Director at KPMG and has worked on financial management projects for various federal agencies, including the Department of Defense. Ventris C. Gibson is nominated for Director of the Mint in the Department of the Treasury. Gibson is currently the Deputy Director of the United States Mint and has a background in senior leadership positions in the federal government, including the Department of Health and Human Services. If confirmed, Gibson will be the first African-American to lead the U.S. Mint.